processes for gathering information about potential short-weighted
seafood adulteration and how to best apply inspectional resources
to this issue. The Committee believes short-weighted labeled prod-
ucts are in violation of the law and that, despite industry reporting
such examples and Committee requests, FDA has not prioritized
enforcement.
